race.comment: GOLD PUMA (11) improving mare. Game performance with the 58kg when she chased right to the line for a sound third over 1310m at Lismore. Can get cover from the draw and close strongly. MONARCH EXPRESS (13) excellent return at Grafton first-up, before chipping away with the 60kg when fifth over 1310m at Lismore. Anywhere near his best can win this. SMART RECOGNITION (3) resumed with two solid wins before heading to the Gold Coast and disappointing when eighth over this trip. Was slow to recover last start and senior rider goes back on. Each-way. FIFTH FORCE (2) got the prize two runs ago in weaker company. Faded in the straight after sitting on the speed to finish eighth over 1805m at Eagle Farm in C3 company. Will relish the claim and drop in trip.
